article.headline: New Orleans 75, North Texas 74
article.story: NEW ORLEANS (AP) -- Jamie McNeilly sank a 14-footer with 4.3 seconds remaining to lift New Orleans to a 75-74 Sun Belt Conference victory over North Texas Saturday night. Jeremie Davis led the Privateers (7-14, 4-6) with 19 points, while McNeilly added 13 and James Parlow and Ernest Daney contributed 10 apiece. New Orleans was down 74-71 after Kendrick Davis hit a jumper with 1:19 to play, but McNeilly scored a basket with 1:02 left to cut the gap to one. Davis then missed a jumper on the ensuing possession, setting up the final game-winning shot for McNeilly. The Mean Green had one last chance but Isaac Hines missed a desperation 3-pointer as time expired. Davis led North Texas (12-9, 5-5) with 25 points. Jeffrey Simpson added 12.
